properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 18 at 4:54PM AKST until January 19 at 6:00AM AKST by NWS Juneau AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...East wind gusts of 60 mph with blowing and falling snow,
especially through gaps. New snow with accumulations of 1 to 2
inches through 8 PM.

* WHERE...Western Prince of Wales Island.

* WHEN...For the Winter Storm Warning, until 8 PM AKST this
evening. For the Winter Weather Advisory, from 8 PM this
evening to 6 AM AKST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Road conditions will be slippery. Strong winds could
cause tree damage. Power outages could occur. Blowing snow could
cause very low visibility and significant drifting.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Wind gusts will diminish to around 35 mph
with more snow of 1 to 3 inches later this evening when a
winter weather advisory is in effect from 8 PM this evening to 6
AM Sunday morning.
properties.instruction:
If you must travel, keep an extra flashlight, food, and water in
your vehicle in case of an emergency.

Slow down and use caution while traveling.

For the latest road conditions call 5 1 1 or visit
511.alaska.gov.
